            <p><add hand="#barker">Order for cattle.</add></p>
        </div1>
        <div1 type="body">
            

<p><placeName>Herculaneum </placeName><date when="1818-11-02">Novr. 2, 1818</date></p>
<p><persName>Mr James Bryan</persName></p>

<p>You have offered to furnish me with some articles to commence
business on <placeName>Red River</placeName>. All I want is as follows four yoke of oxen,
or two yoke of oxen and four Horses Ten Cows and one or two Bulls
When you get to <placeName>Red River</placeName> you can decide whether you will enter
into the Cotton business or not and if you do you can make such<pb n="333"/>
arrangements as you think best&#8212;and if you do not&#8212;you will oblige
me be giveing <persName>Ballard </persName>all the aid in your power</p>

<p>I will account to you for all articles you may furnish at the highest
rates as soon as I am able to do so&#8212;                               <persName>S  F Austin</persName>.</p>

        </div1>
